      Things happen
   =20
 =20
Matt Klein: The Implications of Unrestricted Financial Warfare. Biden Pushe=
s for Coordinated Approach to  Crypto Oversight.=C2=A0Germany Is Stalling E=
U Efforts to Broaden Russia=E2=80=99s  SWIFT Ban. Russia=E2=80=99s techies =
flee country they fear is =E2=80=98flying into an abyss=E2=80=99. How Amban=
i  Outfoxed Amazon in a $3.4 Billion Deal Dispute.=C2=A0Mainstream Hedge Fu=
nds Pour Billions of Dollars Into Crypto. USA Today Owner Gannett Co. Gave =
Advertisers Inaccurate Information for Nine Months.=C2=A0SMBC Nikko complai=
ned to regulators over trader=E2=80=99s death after questioning. Will Russi=
an default lead to another pari passu saga?=C2=A0Gauloises Cigarette Maker =
Halts Russia Operations Amid Sanctions.=C2=A0A-Rod Backs New App That=E2=80=
=99s a =E2=80=98Stock Market=E2=80=99 for  Fans of Athletes. =E2=80=9CThe m=
int Charizard trading card will be auctioned off with other fraudulently ob=
tained luxury items seized by the U.S. Marshals.=E2=80=9DIf you'd like to g=
et=C2=A0Money=C2=A0Stuff=C2=A0in handy email form, right in your inbox, ple=
ase=C2=A0subscribe at this link. Or you can subscribe to Money Stuff and ot=
her great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] Of course careful readers =
of Money Stuff know what you should do if Bobby Kotick calls you and says =
=E2=80=9Chey we=E2=80=99re doing a merger in four days.=E2=80=9D You buy ca=
ll options on, like, Electronic Arts Inc., figuring that *it* will go up on=
 news of a takeover in its industry. In fact EA was up 2.7% on Jan. 18, whi=
le Activision was up 25.9%, so this wouldn=E2=80=99t work out great, but yo=
u also probably wouldn=E2=80=99t get investigated. This is called =E2=80=9C=
 shadow trading=E2=80=9D and hoo boy is it not legal advice! To be clear th=
e SEC thinks it=E2=80=99s illegal! Probably![2] The textbook hedge for sell=
ing a call option is to buy some of the underlying shares, but not all of t=
hem; as the stock goes up you have to buy more shares. (Here my guess is th=
at the delta on the trade date was around 90%, and jumped up to around 96% =
when the deal was announced.) If the stock jumps up discontinuously because=
 of a merger announcement =E2=80=94=C2=A0Activision closed at $65.39 the Fr=
iday before the deal announcement and opened at $86.77 the next day =E2=80=
=94 you lose money, buying lots of stock at a higher price. Other hedges ar=
e possible =E2=80=94=C2=A0JPMorgan could have bought listed options, etc. =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0and for all I know JPMorgan did well on this trade, but my b=
aseline assumption is that it probably didn=E2=80=99t.
